title: Google\Cloud\DocumentAI\V1\BatchProcessMetadata\IndividualProcessStatus
name: IndividualProcessStatus
description:
The status of a each individual document in the batch process.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.documentai.v1.BatchProcessMetadata.IndividualProcessStatus

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.input_gcs_source
params.description: The source of the document, same as the [input_gcs_source] field in the request when the batch process started. The batch process is started by take snapshot of that document, since a user can move or change that document during the process.

params.name: data.output_gcs_destination
params.description: The output_gcs_destination (in the request as output_gcs_destination) of the processed document if it was successful, otherwise empty.

params.name: data.human_review_status
params.description: The status of human review on the processed document.
